					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This records a gift of 96 sheep for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Tiruttāntōṉṟi-Bhaṭṭāra at Tirumaḻalai in Veṇṇāḍu by (a chief ?) <hi rend="bold">Muṭṭaṉ Ēḍuḍaiyār</hi> on behalf of his wife <hi rend="italic">(dēviyār)</hi> <hi rend="bold">Āchchaṉ Kaliyugat-taṉiyugat-tāyār Vīranāraṇiyār.</hi> The <hi rend="italic">sabhā</hi> of the place agreed to maintain the gift. This is probably a record of <hi rend="bold">Uttama-Chōḷa.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
